    "created_at": "2015-06-01T00:02:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-01T00:04:56Z",
    "body": "> We're not asking about the menu, but rather the keybinding. Being able to do Cmd+Opt+I by default to get devtools without any setup is very useful.\n\nIn the default app, the menus _are_ the keybinding, that's the only way those shortcuts get invoked. What we probably need here is a `MenuItem.createDefaultMenus()` that would return a pre-canned menu that sets a lot of these up, then devs can bolt their own menus onto it or remove ones they don't like. \n\nRight now it's too hard to get back to the default behavior, you have to figure out weirdo Selector Magic and stuff on OS X and on other platforms you have to go digging around in webContents. \n"
  },
